sub_title: Urban Analyst & Designer || M.Sc. Metropolitan Analysis, Design and Engineering
summary:
Designer of many things | Passionate about the world and self improvement.

Presently pursuing a Masters of Science in Metropolitan Analysis, Design and Engineering. I hold a Bachelor of Architectural Studies, with a focus in Urbanism from Carleton University.  Beyond my educational credentials however, I have varied interests and skills which define who I am as a person. First and foremost, I consider myself passionate. Be it creative pursuits such as architecture, art, graphic design, writing and cooking -- or personal interests such as rowing, skiing, spending time outdoors, and lowering my own carbon footprint -- I am committed to learning, and self-improvement. 

Through my education and various internships, I have acquired a breadth of transferable skills. I studied architecture and urbanism; where my range of interests expanded exponentially. I have worked at three very different architecture firms: Badrock Studio, Adamson Associates and Dialog Design -- where my technical skills have developed rapidly, but arguably even more important than that, I have learned so much about working with people, solving problems rapidly, and being both a leader and teammate. And whilst unrelated to my professional pursuits, the time I have spent working manual labour in a warehouse has been critically important to my growth as a person. 

It is of utmost importance to me to be a part of a team, and to flourish in a position where I can grow as and individual while helping that team succeed together.
